1
00:00:33,500 --> 00:00:34,958
[AVRIL]
Once upon a time,

2
00:00:35,041 --> 00:00:38,833
in the heart of Saubure's
capital city, Saubreme.

3
00:00:43,916 --> 00:00:47,416
[GIRL sighs] Wow, I wish I
could have a dress like that.

4
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:49,833
[MANNEQUIN]
Why don't you come inside then?

5
00:00:49,916 --> 00:00:52,083
--I can help you.
--[GIRL] Huh?

6
00:00:52,166 --> 00:00:53,958
[MANNEQUIN chuckles]

7
00:00:56,250 --> 00:00:57,541
[AVRIL]
Little did she know

8
00:00:57,625 --> 00:01:00,333
that the moment she entered
the department store...

9
00:01:07,208 --> 00:01:09,833
--[AVRIL screams]
--[KAZUYA screams]

10
00:01:09,916 --> 00:01:11,250
[laughs]

11
00:01:11,333 --> 00:01:13,041
--Oh, I got you so good!
--[sighs]

12
00:01:13,125 --> 00:01:15,041
Little 'Fraidy Cat Kujo!

13
00:01:15,125 --> 00:01:18,375
Well, of course I'll react
if you shout like that!

14
00:01:18,458 --> 00:01:21,083
--Come on, sheesh.
--[AVRIL] Huh?

15
00:01:21,166 --> 00:01:23,041
Looks like you're
about to go shopping!

16
00:01:23,125 --> 00:01:24,625
Yeah. My sister back home

17
00:01:24,708 --> 00:01:27,166
asked if I could send
her a few things.

18
00:01:27,250 --> 00:01:28,666
Let's see.

19
00:01:28,750 --> 00:01:31,041
She lists three white,
cotton blouses.

20
00:01:31,125 --> 00:01:34,166
Then, a separate plaid collar,
warm shoes and socks,

21
00:01:34,250 --> 00:01:37,333
a glass pen and
lastly, a blue rose.

22
00:01:37,416 --> 00:01:39,375
I've never even
heard of a blue rose.

23
00:01:39,458 --> 00:01:41,291
[AVRIL]
You've got to be kidding.

24
00:01:42,333 --> 00:01:44,125
May I present, the blue rose.

25
00:01:44,208 --> 00:01:45,333
Ta-da!

26
00:01:45,416 --> 00:01:46,625
It's a blue diamond.

27
00:01:46,708 --> 00:01:48,958
The national treasure
of the royal family.

28
00:01:49,041 --> 00:01:51,083
But it was stolen
during the last war,

29
00:01:51,166 --> 00:01:53,083
so nobody knows
where it ended up.

30
00:01:53,166 --> 00:01:54,583
[KAZUYA]
Huh.

31
00:01:54,666 --> 00:01:57,375
Your sister probably meant
that she wants a replica of it.

32
00:01:57,458 --> 00:01:59,291
There's a department
store called Jeantan

33
00:01:59,375 --> 00:02:02,083
that sells glass,
blue rose paperweights.

34
00:02:02,166 --> 00:02:03,333
Thanks for the tip.

35
00:02:03,416 --> 00:02:05,666
Aww... But I'm a little jealous.

36
00:02:05,750 --> 00:02:08,416
I wish I could go
shopping in Saubreme.

37
00:02:08,500 --> 00:02:09,916
But, as long as you're going,

38
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,958
you should borrow this
book of ghost stories!

39
00:02:12,041 --> 00:02:14,458
[KAZUYA]
Uh... Great, thank you.

40
00:02:14,541 --> 00:02:16,083
[AVRIL]
By the way, you never told me

41
00:02:16,166 --> 00:02:17,291
what your sister sent you!

42
00:02:17,375 --> 00:02:18,875
[KAZUYA gasps]
That's right!

43
00:02:18,958 --> 00:02:22,250
I better go-- I need
to visit Victorique.

44
00:02:22,333 --> 00:02:25,208
Avril, thanks for all of your
help with my sister's letter.

45
00:02:25,291 --> 00:02:26,500
See you later!

46
00:02:27,666 --> 00:02:29,958
Wait a minute, who in
the world is Victorique?

47
00:04:00,083 --> 00:04:03,333
[VICTORIQUE groans]
I'm bored, I'm bored, I'm bored,

48
00:04:03,416 --> 00:04:06,500
I'm bored, I'm bored, so bored!

49
00:04:06,583 --> 00:04:08,250
If something doesn't
happen soon, I'll--

50
00:04:08,333 --> 00:04:11,958
[KAZUYA panting]

51
00:04:12,041 --> 00:04:14,166
Hey. Sorry I'm so late.

52
00:04:14,250 --> 00:04:15,750
Did you hear the news?

53
00:04:15,833 --> 00:04:18,000
I'm going to Saubreme tomorrow
to pick up some souvenirs for--

54
00:04:18,083 --> 00:04:19,416
[VICTORIQUE]
You'll do no such thing.

55
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:21,708
By tomorrow, you must be
embroiled in a mysterious,

56
00:04:21,791 --> 00:04:23,000
bizarre incident with which

57
00:04:23,083 --> 00:04:24,541
you'll desperately
need assistance.

58
00:04:24,625 --> 00:04:26,125
[KAZUYA]
A-Are you kidding?

59
00:04:26,208 --> 00:04:27,708
--No way!
--No need to worry.

60
00:04:27,791 --> 00:04:29,125
You know I'll solve
it immediately,

61
00:04:29,208 --> 00:04:30,875
once I put my mind to it.

62
00:04:30,958 --> 00:04:32,541
But at least I won't be bored.

63
00:04:32,625 --> 00:04:33,875
[KAZUYA growls]

64
00:04:33,958 --> 00:04:35,625
Oh! That's right.

65
00:04:36,666 --> 00:04:38,041
[KAZUYA]
Here. A present.

66
00:04:38,125 --> 00:04:39,833
That'll distract you for a bit.

67
00:04:39,916 --> 00:04:41,208
A present?

68
00:04:41,291 --> 00:04:43,458
It had better not be another
one of those baffling--

69
00:04:43,541 --> 00:04:44,583
[gasps]

70
00:04:45,833 --> 00:04:46,958
It's so pretty!

71
00:04:47,041 --> 00:04:48,541
They're clothes from my country.

72
00:04:48,625 --> 00:04:50,458
I told my sister all
about you in a letter,

73
00:04:50,541 --> 00:04:52,166
so she wanted to
send them as a gift.

74
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:53,458
If nothing else,
I thought they might

75
00:04:53,541 --> 00:04:55,041
make some good pajamas for you.

76
00:04:55,125 --> 00:04:55,625
Want 'em?

77
00:04:55,708 --> 00:04:56,916
I do!

78
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,333
[KAZUYA chuckles]

79
00:04:58,416 --> 00:05:01,000
I'm glad you like them.
You had me worried for a second.

80
00:05:01,083 --> 00:05:02,541
I should probably show you

81
00:05:02,625 --> 00:05:03,875
how to tie the <i>obi</i> though.
It can be a little--

82
00:05:03,958 --> 00:05:05,916
I don't need your
help figuring it out.

83
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:09,333
You should know that nothing is
beyond my wellspring of wisdom.

84
00:05:09,416 --> 00:05:12,000
You must be joking.
Let me show you, okay?

85
00:05:12,083 --> 00:05:14,375
Look at that, I appear
to be reading a book.

86
00:05:14,458 --> 00:05:16,083
If you don't have
any cases for me,

87
00:05:16,166 --> 00:05:18,250
then leave that here
and get out of my sight.

88
00:05:18,333 --> 00:05:19,916
You're no use to me.

89
00:05:20,000 --> 00:05:22,875
All right... I guess.
If that's what you want,

90
00:05:22,958 --> 00:05:25,916
I do have a few things to
take care of before my trip.

91
00:05:26,958 --> 00:05:28,416
So, good luck with these.

92
00:05:28,500 --> 00:05:30,083
Sorry to bother you.

93
00:05:35,458 --> 00:05:38,208
[VICTORIQUE growls]

94
00:05:42,875 --> 00:05:45,708
[sighs] Pretty!
And it's all mine!

95
00:05:49,958 --> 00:05:51,708
[VICTORIQUE]
♪ New clothes, new clothes! ♪

96
00:05:51,791 --> 00:05:55,208
♪ I... love...
new... clothes... ♪

97
00:05:55,291 --> 00:05:58,541
[hums]

98
00:05:58,625 --> 00:06:00,458
♪ Clothes from Kujo. ♪

99
00:06:00,541 --> 00:06:14,708
[humming continues]

100
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:39,541
Didn't he say that
these were pajamas?

101
00:06:39,625 --> 00:06:41,708
He's really such an idiot.

102
00:06:42,833 --> 00:06:44,083
Is this a belt?

103
00:06:44,166 --> 00:06:45,583
No, there's no buckle.

104
00:06:45,666 --> 00:06:46,791
A ribbon?

105
00:06:46,875 --> 00:06:48,666
But it's way too long.

106
00:06:54,791 --> 00:06:56,125
Utter chaos.

107
00:07:00,833 --> 00:07:03,541
[KAZUYA]
"The Devil-Worshipping Vagrants.

108
00:07:03,625 --> 00:07:06,833
They kidnap children for
their sacrifices, and--"

109
00:07:06,916 --> 00:07:09,166
What the?! "Hang them up
inside of their clothing"?

110
00:07:09,250 --> 00:07:10,458
What kind of ending is that?

111
00:07:10,541 --> 00:07:13,708
[laughs] These stories
are preposterous.

112
00:07:17,708 --> 00:07:22,791
[VICTORIQUE snoring]

113
00:07:27,458 --> 00:07:30,875
[groans]

114
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:40,375
[yawns]

115
00:07:40,458 --> 00:07:42,125
Good morning, Miss Cécile!

116
00:07:42,208 --> 00:07:43,625
[CÉCILE]
Morning, Kujo!

117
00:07:43,708 --> 00:07:44,916
You have perfect timing.

118
00:07:45,000 --> 00:07:47,416
I was looking-- [yelps]

119
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:48,833
[whimpers]

120
00:07:48,916 --> 00:07:50,083
Are you all right?

121
00:07:50,166 --> 00:07:52,250
Can't find my glasses...

122
00:07:52,333 --> 00:07:53,291
Help me.

123
00:07:53,375 --> 00:07:55,916
Here you go.
You sure you're okay?

124
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:58,041
[CÉCILE] I'll be fine!
You're such a gentleman.

125
00:07:58,125 --> 00:07:59,541
Thank you, Kujo.

126
00:07:59,625 --> 00:08:01,375
Oh! But there's
no time for that!

127
00:08:01,458 --> 00:08:03,625
I need you to listen and
try not to be alarmed.

128
00:08:03,708 --> 00:08:05,083
Something's wrong
with Victorique!

129
00:08:05,166 --> 00:08:06,208
[gasps]

130
00:08:06,291 --> 00:08:07,458
[sneezes]

131
00:08:08,958 --> 00:08:11,125
[door opens]

132
00:08:11,208 --> 00:08:12,291
[CÉCILE]
Here.

133
00:08:12,375 --> 00:08:14,291
It's a message from Kujo.

134
00:08:17,916 --> 00:08:20,583
[KAZUYA] Victorique, I'm sorry
to hear you caught a cold.

135
00:08:20,666 --> 00:08:22,208
You must feel pretty stupid.

136
00:08:22,291 --> 00:08:25,125
This is how you tie
an <i>obi</i> , by the way.

137
00:08:25,208 --> 00:08:27,791
--[VICTORIQUE growls]
--[CÉCILE] He sent this, too.

138
00:08:27,875 --> 00:08:29,916
I bet you could use it to
keep your boredom at bay.

139
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:33,083
Kujo went all the way to the
dorm just to get it for you.

140
00:08:33,166 --> 00:08:35,291
[VICTORIQUE sneezes]

141
00:08:35,375 --> 00:08:36,541
[CÉCILE laughs]

142
00:08:39,291 --> 00:08:41,875
Huh. I didn't know she
had a house out here.

143
00:08:41,958 --> 00:08:43,458
[door opens]

144
00:08:43,541 --> 00:08:44,666
[KAZUYA]
How is she?

145
00:08:44,750 --> 00:08:46,875
[CÉCILE]
Well, her face is bright red.

146
00:08:46,958 --> 00:08:48,875
And she's sneezing a lot.

147
00:08:53,375 --> 00:08:54,666
"Idiot"?!

148
00:08:54,750 --> 00:08:55,500
Oh, my!

149
00:08:55,583 --> 00:08:56,916
That ungrateful...

150
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,958
You're the idiot,
do you hear me?

151
00:08:59,041 --> 00:09:01,416
Mean girls like you
shouldn't even get presents!

152
00:09:01,500 --> 00:09:03,666
I'm leaving! Bye!

153
00:09:04,833 --> 00:09:07,041
Get presents?

154
00:09:07,125 --> 00:09:09,750
[door opens, closes]

155
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:13,250
[VICTORIQUE]
Hi, Cécile. Is Kujo leaving?

156
00:09:13,333 --> 00:09:14,166
[CÉCILE]
Yeah...

157
00:09:14,250 --> 00:09:15,833
He says he's going to Saubreme.

158
00:09:15,916 --> 00:09:18,500
He has some things he
needs to buy, I think.

159
00:09:18,583 --> 00:09:20,708
[VICTORIQUE]
He's really going now?

160
00:09:21,875 --> 00:09:25,166
I guess he couldn't be bothered
to wait for me to go with him.

161
00:09:25,250 --> 00:09:27,208
That selfish brat.

162
00:09:27,291 --> 00:09:29,750
[sneezes]

163
00:09:37,666 --> 00:09:39,250
--[door opens]
--[BLOIS] Excuse me.

164
00:09:39,333 --> 00:09:41,666
Are these seats taken--? Uh!

165
00:09:45,583 --> 00:09:46,791
Oh. It's you.

166
00:09:46,875 --> 00:09:48,333
Little Squirrel.

167
00:09:48,416 --> 00:09:49,583
What a surprise.

168
00:09:49,666 --> 00:09:51,875
The police headquarters
in Saubreme has asked me

169
00:09:51,958 --> 00:09:55,208
to lend my assistance
with a particular case.

170
00:09:55,291 --> 00:09:57,625
It's rumored that several
priceless works of art,

171
00:09:57,708 --> 00:09:59,125
which were stolen
during the war,

172
00:09:59,208 --> 00:10:01,791
have been showing up on the
black market there lately.

173
00:10:01,875 --> 00:10:03,666
And so, of course,
the higher-ups...

174
00:10:03,750 --> 00:10:05,916
[KAZUYA] I really hope that
Victorique is feeling better

175
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,625
and resting well, now.

176
00:10:09,083 --> 00:10:12,208
[KAZUYA]
She's such a tiny little thing.

177
00:10:12,291 --> 00:10:13,458
She's bossy...

178
00:10:13,541 --> 00:10:16,625
And hot tempered,
and a bit of a devil.

179
00:10:16,708 --> 00:10:20,166
But for some reason, I can't
help caring about her.

180
00:10:21,291 --> 00:10:22,208
[KAZUYA]
And...

181
00:10:22,291 --> 00:10:24,333
I know she cares for me, too.

182
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,833
Your two hearts are connected.

183
00:10:27,916 --> 00:10:30,166
And always will be.

184
00:10:30,250 --> 00:10:33,375
[KAZUYA] She risked her
life to save me that night.

185
00:10:33,458 --> 00:10:36,083
She seemed so afraid.

186
00:10:36,166 --> 00:10:37,875
And as if that wasn't enough,

187
00:10:37,958 --> 00:10:41,791
I've also been informed there's
been a series of disappearances.

188
00:10:41,875 --> 00:10:44,291
Young women and children
keep vanishing.

189
00:10:44,375 --> 00:10:46,333
They go out shopping,
and then all of a sudden,

190
00:10:46,416 --> 00:10:48,208
--they're gone.
--[KAZUYA] Why?

191
00:10:48,291 --> 00:10:51,625
Why, of all people, did it have
to be you here with me today?

192
00:10:51,708 --> 00:10:55,041
Well, my sentiments,
exactly! Hmph!

193
00:10:55,125 --> 00:10:56,666
Careful out there, Squirrel.

194
00:10:56,750 --> 00:10:58,166
Don't let yourself
get swallowed up

195
00:10:58,250 --> 00:11:00,833
by the dark, scary metropolis.

196
00:11:00,916 --> 00:11:02,125
I'll be fine.

197
00:11:02,208 --> 00:11:03,416
--[DRIVER grunts]
--[horse neighs]

198
00:11:22,958 --> 00:11:24,208
[LUIGI]
Sauburean.

199
00:11:24,291 --> 00:11:25,458
Sauburean.

200
00:11:25,541 --> 00:11:26,500
Italian.

201
00:11:26,583 --> 00:11:28,916
Sauburean. Swiss.

202
00:11:30,375 --> 00:11:32,083
[LUIGI]
Chinese?

203
00:11:37,333 --> 00:11:40,833
[KAZUYA]
So, this is Jeantan...

204
00:11:40,916 --> 00:11:42,416
[gulps]

205
00:11:49,375 --> 00:11:50,625
Well, here I am.

206
00:11:50,708 --> 00:11:52,625
Where are the blue roses?

207
00:11:56,583 --> 00:11:58,166
[CLERK]
Hello, sir.

208
00:11:58,250 --> 00:12:00,750
If I may ask, where're
you visiting from?

209
00:12:00,833 --> 00:12:02,041
[KAZUYA]
Oh! Sure.

210
00:12:02,125 --> 00:12:03,458
I'm from the East.

211
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:06,875
Blue Roses can be
found on the top floor.

212
00:12:06,958 --> 00:12:08,208
Shall I show you the way now?

213
00:12:08,291 --> 00:12:11,208
No thanks. I'm pretty
sure I've got it.

214
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:15,750
--[elevator dings]
--[doors rattle]

215
00:12:21,708 --> 00:12:22,708
[KAZUYA]
I think...

216
00:12:22,791 --> 00:12:24,791
This is where he said to go.

217
00:12:29,791 --> 00:12:31,208
[KAZUYA]
Excuse me?

218
00:12:31,291 --> 00:12:32,250
[gasps]

219
00:12:35,750 --> 00:12:37,250
[KAZUYA]
There it is!

220
00:12:43,791 --> 00:12:44,666
[GARNIER]
Who's there?!

221
00:12:44,750 --> 00:12:45,750
[gasps]

222
00:12:48,291 --> 00:12:50,625
[GARNIER]
Hey! Kid! Who're you?

223
00:12:51,875 --> 00:12:54,166
[KAZUYA]
Just a patron!

224
00:12:54,250 --> 00:12:56,250
[GARNIER]
What are you doing in here?

225
00:12:57,291 --> 00:12:59,375
I heard this was where
I could buy a Blue Rose.

226
00:12:59,458 --> 00:13:00,500
[GARNIER gasps]

227
00:13:04,541 --> 00:13:06,625
[GARNIER grunts]
Paperweights are in Stationary

228
00:13:06,708 --> 00:13:10,500
on the second level.
On your way, then, young man.

229
00:13:10,583 --> 00:13:11,958
Yes, sir, but--

230
00:13:15,708 --> 00:13:17,625
I'm sorry to disturb you.

231
00:13:19,166 --> 00:13:22,083
[GARNIER] Even if he does match
the description we were given,

232
00:13:22,166 --> 00:13:24,583
no one would send a child
as their messenger.

233
00:13:24,666 --> 00:13:26,166
Tell our men on the lower floor.

234
00:13:26,250 --> 00:13:28,250
Yes, of course. Right away, sir.

235
00:13:28,333 --> 00:13:30,583
And make the
arrangements at once.

236
00:13:32,208 --> 00:13:34,250
[sighs]

237
00:13:34,333 --> 00:13:35,291
Shame on me.

238
00:13:35,375 --> 00:13:37,125
The third son of
an imperial soldier

239
00:13:37,208 --> 00:13:40,833
shouldn't engage in shenanigans
like eavesdropping.

240
00:13:40,916 --> 00:13:42,625
However...

241
00:13:42,708 --> 00:13:45,166
[KAZUYA] That beautiful
woman intrigued me.

242
00:13:45,250 --> 00:13:48,500
Her expression...
It was so cold.

243
00:13:48,583 --> 00:13:50,875
She reminded me of a mannequin.

244
00:13:55,583 --> 00:13:57,000
[KAZUYA]
Oh, no!

245
00:13:57,083 --> 00:13:58,833
This must be the
service elevator.

246
00:13:58,916 --> 00:14:00,041
I need to go back up--

247
00:14:00,125 --> 00:14:02,000
--[thud]
--[gasps]

248
00:14:04,583 --> 00:14:07,291
[KAZUYA]
Hello? Is someone down here?

249
00:14:18,958 --> 00:14:21,916
[gasps]

250
00:14:23,416 --> 00:14:24,833
[KAZUYA]
Mannequins?

251
00:14:33,250 --> 00:14:34,916
[gulps]

252
00:14:39,750 --> 00:14:41,458
[gasps]

253
00:14:41,541 --> 00:14:43,208
[sighs]

254
00:14:44,208 --> 00:14:46,625
[KAZUYA]
Okay, she's one of them, too.

255
00:14:46,708 --> 00:14:48,958
Wait a minute,
something's isn't--

256
00:14:49,041 --> 00:14:52,791
Why is she the only
mannequin with closed eyes?

257
00:14:52,875 --> 00:14:55,333
--[ANASTASIA gasps]
--[KAZUYA screams]

258
00:14:55,416 --> 00:14:57,416
[gasping]

259
00:14:57,500 --> 00:15:00,833
A devil! There's a devil!

260
00:15:00,916 --> 00:15:02,166
So many...

261
00:15:02,250 --> 00:15:04,250
They're coming for us!

262
00:15:04,333 --> 00:15:05,333
We're going to die!

263
00:15:05,416 --> 00:15:07,208
Miss, please, you
have to calm down!

264
00:15:07,291 --> 00:15:08,875
You shouldn't be in
a place like this.

265
00:15:08,958 --> 00:15:10,375
I'll call someone from
the store right away!

266
00:15:10,458 --> 00:15:11,916
[ANASTASIA]
No! The police!

267
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:13,875
--You have to call the police!
--[KAZUYA yelps]

268
00:15:13,958 --> 00:15:15,750
[groans]

269
00:15:16,916 --> 00:15:18,958
Okay, that hurt-- [gasps]

270
00:15:20,708 --> 00:15:23,041
[KAZUYA]
Hello? Miss?

271
00:15:27,208 --> 00:15:30,166
[BLOIS] Well? Is that
all you have to say?

272
00:15:30,250 --> 00:15:32,250
Yes. Please send some
officers to Jean--

273
00:15:32,333 --> 00:15:34,416
[BLOIS] I've had quite
enough of this nonsense.

274
00:15:34,500 --> 00:15:36,958
As you might've guessed,
we're extremely busy.

275
00:15:37,041 --> 00:15:39,666
Inspector! There's a girl
there who's in trouble!

276
00:15:39,750 --> 00:15:41,625
She told me to call
the police to get help!

277
00:15:41,708 --> 00:15:42,875
This is a solid case!

278
00:15:42,958 --> 00:15:45,583
--You have to believe me!
--[yawns]

279
00:15:45,666 --> 00:15:47,875
--Superintendent General!
--[BLOIS gasps]

280
00:15:47,958 --> 00:15:49,375
Welcome.

281
00:15:49,458 --> 00:15:50,958
Grévil!

282
00:15:52,041 --> 00:15:53,791
It's been quite a while.

283
00:15:53,875 --> 00:15:56,791
You haven't been by the house
to see us in such a long time.

284
00:15:56,875 --> 00:15:59,625
Jacqueline can't help
worrying, you know.

285
00:15:59,708 --> 00:16:02,000
Yes, well, it's just that
I've been so busy that I--

286
00:16:02,083 --> 00:16:04,166
[SIGNORE]
I've heard of your fine work.

287
00:16:04,250 --> 00:16:05,833
I have high hopes
that your unique gifts

288
00:16:05,916 --> 00:16:07,166
will be a tremendous asset to us

289
00:16:07,250 --> 00:16:09,833
in breaking this
art smuggling case.

290
00:16:13,791 --> 00:16:16,000
--Look alive there, boy!
--[gasps]

291
00:16:16,083 --> 00:16:16,958
Come on!

292
00:16:17,041 --> 00:16:17,958
[KAZUYA]
Yes... sir!

293
00:16:18,041 --> 00:16:20,125
[BLOIS]
Pardon us, this is urgent.

294
00:16:20,208 --> 00:16:22,208
Right. Of course.

295
00:16:23,958 --> 00:16:25,250
[KAZUYA]
I'm grateful for the help,

296
00:16:25,333 --> 00:16:27,375
but why did you suddenly
change your mind?

297
00:16:27,458 --> 00:16:29,750
You said it yourself,
didn't you?

298
00:16:29,833 --> 00:16:33,458
It sounds like there's something
mysterious going on at Jeantan.

299
00:16:33,541 --> 00:16:35,833
And it's important for me
to meet the expectations

300
00:16:35,916 --> 00:16:39,166
being placed on me.
Especially now.

301
00:16:42,291 --> 00:16:43,708
--[BLOIS] So?
--[KAZUYA] Okay.

302
00:16:43,791 --> 00:16:46,375
The first thing I did was ask
that gentleman over there

303
00:16:46,458 --> 00:16:49,291
where they sell the
Blue Rose paperweights.

304
00:16:49,375 --> 00:16:52,625
I'm sorry to say, I've never
seen this young man before.

305
00:16:52,708 --> 00:16:54,041
[KAZUYA gasps]

306
00:16:54,125 --> 00:16:55,958
But it was just a little while
ago, don't you remember?

307
00:16:56,041 --> 00:17:01,750
You asked where I was from--

308
00:17:01,833 --> 00:17:03,833
[BLOIS]
What are you playing at, Kujo?

309
00:17:03,916 --> 00:17:06,416
[GARNIER]
Is there a problem, gentlemen?

310
00:17:07,041 --> 00:17:09,500
I'm Garnier, the owner,
and I'm glad to help.

311
00:17:09,583 --> 00:17:11,166
How can I be of
assistance today?

312
00:17:11,250 --> 00:17:13,416
Sir. We met earlier upstairs.

313
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:14,541
I had gotten lost, and--

314
00:17:14,625 --> 00:17:15,916
[GARNIER]
I'm afraid you're mistaken.

315
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:17,083
[KAZUYA gasps]

316
00:17:21,166 --> 00:17:23,000
Well, in the room
on the top floor,

317
00:17:23,083 --> 00:17:24,416
behind the big, oak door,

318
00:17:24,500 --> 00:17:26,583
there were these...
glass cases, and they had--

319
00:17:26,666 --> 00:17:27,875
[GARNIER]
Can you explain to me

320
00:17:27,958 --> 00:17:30,833
what this Oriental
boy is talking about?

321
00:17:30,916 --> 00:17:32,208
Well, uh...

322
00:17:32,291 --> 00:17:33,500
The door was oak.

323
00:17:33,583 --> 00:17:34,833
And the paper was brown.

324
00:17:34,916 --> 00:17:37,041
And there were black and
white tiles on the floor

325
00:17:37,125 --> 00:17:38,625
in a checkerboard pattern.

326
00:17:38,708 --> 00:17:40,208
Take me to that room, please.

327
00:17:40,291 --> 00:17:42,000
It's important that I
prove to the inspector

328
00:17:42,083 --> 00:17:44,166
that I'm telling the truth.

329
00:17:44,250 --> 00:17:45,666
Fine.

330
00:17:48,625 --> 00:17:49,666
[KAZUYA gasps]

331
00:17:50,875 --> 00:17:52,041
Boy...

332
00:17:53,375 --> 00:17:55,208
No way. It can't be.

333
00:17:55,291 --> 00:17:57,750
Satisfied now, young man?

334
00:18:03,208 --> 00:18:04,125
[KAZUYA]
This is it.

335
00:18:04,208 --> 00:18:05,875
There was a girl in here.

336
00:18:08,125 --> 00:18:09,083
[gasps]

337
00:18:10,750 --> 00:18:12,125
[KAZUYA]
A mannequin?

338
00:18:13,791 --> 00:18:15,875
But I know she
was in this crate.

339
00:18:16,916 --> 00:18:19,333
[BLOIS] What is the
meaning of this, Kujo?

340
00:18:20,375 --> 00:18:21,958
[GARNIER laughs]

341
00:18:22,041 --> 00:18:24,541
You mean, this poor
kid actually mistook

342
00:18:24,625 --> 00:18:26,208
a mannequin for a person?

343
00:18:26,291 --> 00:18:27,750
I've seen it all.

344
00:18:27,833 --> 00:18:29,041
Waste of my time.

345
00:18:29,125 --> 00:18:31,583
No, you're wrong!
You have to believe me!

346
00:18:31,666 --> 00:18:33,541
There really was a girl here!

347
00:18:33,625 --> 00:18:35,125
She even spoke to me!

348
00:18:35,208 --> 00:18:36,833
--[BLOIS] I'm too busy for this.
--Find her. She can't have

349
00:18:36,916 --> 00:18:38,708
--gotten very far.
--Right.

350
00:18:39,750 --> 00:18:40,958
[gasps]

351
00:18:48,291 --> 00:18:49,958
[VICTORIQUE]
Bored.

352
00:18:53,291 --> 00:18:56,583
[thunder claps]

353
00:19:00,916 --> 00:19:02,416
I'm so bored.

354
00:19:02,500 --> 00:19:05,416
It'll be the death
of me at this rate.

355
00:19:05,500 --> 00:19:09,291
Could someone... bring
me a book or something?

356
00:19:11,750 --> 00:19:13,250
Please, save me...

357
00:19:13,333 --> 00:19:14,583
[gasps]

358
00:19:14,666 --> 00:19:17,583
What'd you say?
Do you need something?

359
00:19:21,791 --> 00:19:24,083
[CÉCILE]
Oh dear, your fever's worse.

360
00:19:24,166 --> 00:19:25,500
I'm afraid you'll need a shot.

361
00:19:25,583 --> 00:19:26,875
[VICTORIQUE]
No!

362
00:19:26,958 --> 00:19:29,458
You can't make me!
I'm never coming out of here!

363
00:19:29,541 --> 00:19:30,708
My goodness.

364
00:19:30,791 --> 00:19:33,041
It'll be over quickly
if you don't fight!

365
00:19:33,125 --> 00:19:34,125
[VICTORIQUE]
I hate this!

366
00:19:34,208 --> 00:19:35,541
Why can't you be like Kujo?

367
00:19:35,625 --> 00:19:39,083
He always does what
I sa-ah--! [sneezes]

368
00:19:40,125 --> 00:19:43,458
Kujo, you big fool.
Why aren't you back yet?

369
00:19:43,541 --> 00:19:45,250
Surely, there's no way
he could've actually

370
00:19:45,333 --> 00:19:47,625
gotten himself involved
in a case, is there?

371
00:19:47,708 --> 00:19:49,666
[sneezes]

372
00:19:49,750 --> 00:19:51,916
[groans]

373
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:53,583
[BLOIS]
Give me a break, Squirrel!

374
00:19:53,666 --> 00:19:55,458
None of the clerks
saw you there!

375
00:19:55,541 --> 00:19:57,958
The room you claim you
went to doesn't exist!

376
00:19:58,041 --> 00:20:00,208
Neither does the girl,
for that matter.

377
00:20:00,291 --> 00:20:02,708
[KAZUYA] Inspector!
I swear, I wouldn't lie!

378
00:20:02,791 --> 00:20:04,416
I don't want to
hear another word.

379
00:20:04,500 --> 00:20:07,083
Go finish up your shopping
and head back home.

380
00:20:13,500 --> 00:20:15,791
I don't get what's
going on in this city.

381
00:20:15,875 --> 00:20:17,166
--[OLD WOMAN grunts]
--[KAZUYA yelps]

382
00:20:17,250 --> 00:20:18,583
My daughter...

383
00:20:18,666 --> 00:20:20,958
My daughter, she was eaten up!

384
00:20:21,041 --> 00:20:22,041
[KAZUYA]
She what?!

385
00:20:22,125 --> 00:20:23,916
She was eaten...
by that place, there!

386
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:26,083
My daughter, she was
eaten by that place!

387
00:20:26,166 --> 00:20:27,541
She's there, inside!

388
00:20:27,625 --> 00:20:29,000
Please help me! Please!

389
00:20:29,083 --> 00:20:30,416
[KAZUYA]
The way she's dressed...

390
00:20:30,500 --> 00:20:32,250
It's like the
picture in the book.

391
00:20:32,333 --> 00:20:34,250
The devil-worshipping kidnapper.

392
00:20:34,333 --> 00:20:35,791
--[OLD WOMAN grunts]
--[KAZUYA screams]

393
00:20:37,041 --> 00:20:38,625
[LUIGI]
Nine hundred and fifty-seven.

394
00:20:38,708 --> 00:20:39,666
[OLD WOMAN gasps]

395
00:20:39,750 --> 00:20:40,666
[KAZUYA gasps]

396
00:20:40,750 --> 00:20:43,125
[LUIGI]
Come on! Leave him alone.

397
00:20:43,208 --> 00:20:45,500
You know they're
gonna come back.

398
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:49,166
Who are you?

399
00:20:49,250 --> 00:20:51,791
I'll be taking one of
these, okay, Chinese?

400
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:55,291
[chuckles] Hey, let's cooperate.

401
00:20:55,375 --> 00:20:57,708
I was thinking I could
tell you something useful.

402
00:20:57,791 --> 00:20:58,750
Yeah?

403
00:21:00,208 --> 00:21:02,208
At about 11:50 today...

404
00:21:02,291 --> 00:21:04,916
A group of men went in
the back door of Jeantan.

405
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:07,166
And they had an awful
lot of cargo with 'em.

406
00:21:07,250 --> 00:21:09,583
--[KAZUYA] Like what?
--Well...

407
00:21:09,666 --> 00:21:12,541
Tin cans of paint
and some carpeting.

408
00:21:12,625 --> 00:21:16,041
And big rolls of some kind
of fancy golden paper.

409
00:21:16,125 --> 00:21:18,625
[gasps] Interior decorators!

410
00:21:18,708 --> 00:21:20,708
That means while I was
off talking to the police,

411
00:21:20,791 --> 00:21:23,000
they were busy changing
that room's décor!

412
00:21:23,083 --> 00:21:24,125
[LUIGI]
Yep!

413
00:21:24,208 --> 00:21:26,791
So, I can have one
of these now, right?

414
00:21:26,875 --> 00:21:28,458
[KAZUYA]
What's going on?

415
00:21:28,541 --> 00:21:31,750
It's obvious something weird
is happening at Jeantan.

416
00:21:31,833 --> 00:21:33,333
But what could it be?

417
00:21:33,416 --> 00:21:34,791
You know I'll solve
it immediately,

418
00:21:34,875 --> 00:21:36,458
once I put my mind to it.

419
00:21:36,541 --> 00:21:38,333
But at least I won't be bored.

420
00:21:39,416 --> 00:21:41,750
Hey. I need to ask
you one more thing.

421
00:21:41,833 --> 00:21:42,916
[LUIGI]
Hm?

422
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:44,833
Are there any public
phones around here?

423
00:21:46,125 --> 00:21:48,125
I said I don't like pain, okay?

424
00:21:48,208 --> 00:21:49,958
But the pain is why
it works, my dear.

425
00:21:50,041 --> 00:21:52,041
[VICTORIQUE]
You're a liar! [sneezes]

426
00:21:52,125 --> 00:21:54,583
Now. Hold out your arm, please.

427
00:21:54,666 --> 00:21:57,166
There's a telephone
call for you, Victorique.

428
00:21:57,250 --> 00:21:58,750
That's unexpected.

429
00:21:58,833 --> 00:21:59,750
Who would call me?

430
00:21:59,833 --> 00:22:01,166
[CÉCILE]
Go ahead.

431
00:22:03,500 --> 00:22:05,833
[KAZUYA]
Hello? Hello?

432
00:22:05,916 --> 00:22:06,916
Oh, Kujo!

433
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:08,791
[KAZUYA sighs]
You finally answered!

434
00:22:08,875 --> 00:22:10,791
Victorique, there's
an emergency!

435
00:22:10,875 --> 00:22:12,750
I need you to focus
and listen to me.

436
00:22:12,833 --> 00:22:15,875
The truth is, I really
need your help.

437
00:22:15,958 --> 00:22:17,041
[VICTORIQUE yelps]

438
00:22:21,833 --> 00:22:24,208
[KAZUYA]
"Gyick"? Who's Gyick?

439
00:22:24,291 --> 00:22:26,958
Victorique, stop
playing around--

440
00:22:27,041 --> 00:22:30,250
[screams]

441
00:22:30,333 --> 00:22:31,416
[VICTORIQUE gasps]

442
00:22:33,166 --> 00:22:34,958
Hey, Kujo?

443
00:22:37,666 --> 00:22:39,083
He hung up.

444
00:22:48,708 --> 00:22:50,875
What on earth's
going on around here?

445
00:24:31,791 --> 00:24:35,625
[VICTORIQUE] ♪ I do not
like get-ting shots! ♪

446
00:24:35,708 --> 00:24:39,416
♪ No, I don't,
don't like shots! ♪

447
00:24:39,500 --> 00:24:42,708
[KAZUYA] Sure sounds
like she's having fun.

448
00:24:42,791 --> 00:24:45,041
[VICTORIQUE]
♪ No, I don't ♪

